# Mobile app — React Native Reusables + Expo Router

This skill is the operating manual for `frontend/apps/mobile/`. The codebase
is early-stage but its conventions are already set: shadcn-style UI under
`components/ui/`, NativeWind for styling, `@rn-primitives/*` for
accessibility, CVA for variants, and a deliberate two-layer theme. Match these
patterns rather than improvising — they're what makes future RNR components
drop in cleanly.

## Stack at a glance

- **Expo SDK 54** with New Architecture, React Compiler, and typed routes all
  enabled (see `frontend/apps/mobile/app.json`).
- **expo-router 6** — file-based routing under `app/`.
- **NativeWind 4** — Tailwind classes on React Native. Config in
  `tailwind.config.js`, CSS vars in `global.css`, Metro/Babel wired in
  `metro.config.js` and `babel.config.js`.
- **React Native Reusables (RNR)** via the shadcn CLI — config in
  `components.json` (style `new-york`, aliases pre-set). Components land in
  `components/ui/`.
- **`@rn-primitives/*`** — headless, accessible primitives (`slot`, `portal`,
  `accordion`). Always prefer these over plain `react-native` components when
  building reusable UI.
- **CVA** (`class-variance-authority`) + **`clsx`** + **`tailwind-merge`** —
  variant management. The `cn()` helper at `lib/utils.ts` is the only correct
  way to combine classes.
- **lucide-react-native** — icons. Named imports, `color` + `size` props.
- **@tanstack/react-query** — installed, not yet wired. Mount the
  `QueryClientProvider` in `app/_layout.tsx` when the first network screen
  arrives.
- **`@pkka/api`** (workspace package) — Orval-generated OpenAPI clients. This
  is where data fetching hooks live.

